.Dd @MONTH@ @DAY@, @YEAR@
.Dt IRCCDCTL 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm irccdctl
.Nd irccd controller utility
.\" SYNOPSIS
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm irccdctl
.Op Fl v
.Op Fl c Ar config
.Ar command
.Ar parameters
.Pp
This is the list of commands supported by
.Ns Nm
utility:
.Pp
.\" CNOTICE
.Nm
.Cm cnotice
.Ar server
.Ar channel
.Ar message
.\" HELP
.Nm
.Cm help
.Ar subject
.\" INVITE
.Nm
.Cm invite
.Ar server
.Ar target
.Ar channel
.\" JOIN
.Nm
.Cm join
.Ar server
.Ar channel
.Op Ar password
.\" KICK
.Nm
.Cm kick
.Ar server
.Ar nickname
.Ar channel
.Op Ar reason
.\" LOAD
.Nm
.Cm load
.Ar name
.\" ME
.Nm
.Cm me
.Ar server
.Ar target
.Ar message
.\" MESSAGE
.Nm
.Cm message
.Ar server
.Ar target
.Ar message
.\" MODE
.Nm
.Cm mode
.Ar server
.Ar channel
.Ar mode
.\" NICK
.Nm
.Cm nick
.Ar server
.Ar newnickname
.\" NOTICE
.Nm
.Cm notice
.Ar server
.Ar nickname
.Ar message
.\" PART
.Nm
.Cm part
.Ar server
.Ar channel
.\" RELOAD
.Nm
.Cm reload
.Ar name
.\" TOPIC
.Nm
.Cm topic
.Ar server
.Ar channel
.Ar topic
.\" UMODE
.Nm
.Cm umode
.Ar server
.Ar mode
.\" UNLOAD
.Nm
.Cm unload
.Ar name
.\" DESCRIPTION
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm irccdctl
utility provides serveral options to manipulate a running
irccd instance.
.Pp
It uses sockets to do a basic IPC messaging with irccd, you can use unix
or internet domain sockets.
.Pp
The following options are available:
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It Fl c Ar config
A path to a config file.
.It Fl v
Be more verbose.
.El
.\" SEE ALSO
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr irccd 1 ,
.Xr irccdctl.conf 5
